            <div class="p402_hide"><p class="article-first-paragraph">
  CHERRIES boss <a href="https://www.bournemouthecho.co.uk/search/?search=Eddie+Howe&amp;topic_id=886" target="_self">Eddie Howe</a> will play the waiting game over Adam Smith after the full-back was forced off against Huddersfield.
</p>
<p>
  Smith tried to play through a hamstring problem which he sustained early on at John Smith&rsquo;s Stadium but aggravated the injury just before half-time.
</p>
<p>
  The ex-Tottenham ace was replaced by Nathaniel Clyne, who played his part in a 2-0 success for the visitors.
</p>
<p>
  Howe said: &ldquo;Adam was a hamstring problem so we will wait and see over the extent of that.
</p>
<p>
  &ldquo;I think he felt it very early in the match and carried on and then felt it again, so he knew he had to come off.&rdquo;
</p><div id="inArticleAd-1" class="advert-container"><div id="DFP_in_article_mpu"></div></div>
<p>
  David Brooks, who made his comeback from an ankle injury at the start of this month, also exited the action, this time after an hour.
</p>
<p>
  But having replaced the Welsh international with Dominic Solanke, Howe suggested Brooks was not a major concern.
</p>
<p>
  Howe said: &ldquo;I think David is okay. I don&rsquo;t know, I need to check. I think his was more cramp due to the fact he had been out so long.&rdquo;
</p>
